    <fr:title text="Data parallelism">Data parallelism</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A form of parallelism where the model is replicated across multiple devices and performed on different data.</html:p>
    <html:ul><html:li>Data sharding: data is split across multiple devices i.e. 32 samples and 8 devices results in 4 unique samples per device.</html:li>
    <html:li>Parameter replication: on each device, we need to replcicate the model parameters to run the forward pass for the unique samples.</html:li>
    <html:li>Gradient aggregation: backward pass we need to perform an <html:em>all-reduce</html:em> to sum and average the gradients across devices. This is automatically done by <html:code>@nnx.jit</html:code>.</html:li></html:ul>
  </fr:mainmatter>
